fire, theft, and boys.

28
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:04,710
Date someone you really know, like...

29
00:02:04,710 --> 00:02:06,610
Senior Brother Lin!

30
00:02:07,230 --> 00:02:10,660
Have you seen Senior Brother Lin since you've come to college?

31
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:14,830
- I... 
 - Weren't we talking about where to hang out to have some fun?

32
00:02:14,830 --> 00:02:17,140
Why bring him up?

33
00:02:20,270 --> 00:02:21,700
After your military training,

34
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:23,390
I can drive you guys around.

35
00:02:23,390 --> 00:02:24,770
I'll drive my dad's Mercedes-Benz.

36
00:02:24,770 --> 00:02:26,520
Oh, please. What century is this?

37
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,920
Don't do that. It's cringey.

38
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:35,220
Then, how about going to a bar?

39
00:02:36,930 --> 00:02:38,370
Have you ever been to one?

40
00:02:38,370 --> 00:02:39,700
You?

41
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:40,720
Neither of you have?

42
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:43,571
Let me tell you. This guy from JUFE's basketball team told me,

43
00:02:43,571 --> 00:02:45,670
bars are crazy fun.

44
00:02:45,670 --> 00:02:47,360
Live music, dancing, disco.

45
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:49,360
Can we think of something healthier?

46
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:52,060
Something more classy.

47
00:02:52,060 --> 00:02:54,200
Classy?

48
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,990
How about going to a musical then?

49
00:02:56,990 --> 00:02:58,860
The Grand Theater has a show coming up in a few days.

50
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:01,060
You know Hamlet?

51
00:03:03,270 --> 00:03:05,990
♪ To be and not to be... ♪

52
00:03:05,990 --> 00:03:08,590
If they act like you, then I'm skipping it.

53
00:03:09,430 --> 00:03:11,010
Let's just go to the beach.

54
00:03:11,010 --> 00:03:13,560
Sun, sand, and waves.

55
00:03:14,270 --> 00:03:17,110
Are you some random loafer or a college student?

56
00:03:17,110 --> 00:03:18,670
Why are you all over the place?

57
00:03:18,670 --> 00:03:20,800
Then you tell me, what is appropriate for a college student?

58
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,540
It's my first year, too.

59
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:24,520
I don't know either.

60
00:03:28,340 --> 00:03:31,710
You... do you know where Zhou Shiyun ended up going?

61
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:36,760
She... I heard she didn't get into UST.

62
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:38,540
But I don't know where she actually went.

63
00:03:38,540 --> 00:03:40,700
I haven't been in touch with her family lately.

64
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:43,150
She's actually with Yi Tianyu now.

65
00:03:43,150 --> 00:03:45,330
At JUFE (Jinghai University of Finance &amp; Economics).

66
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:49,170
Bad luck, right?

67
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:50,760
How can you say that?

68
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:53,100
What's unlucky about going to the same college as me?

69
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:55,540
Your getting into JUFE was lucky.

70
00:03:55,540 --> 00:04:00,420
But Zhou Shiyun ending up there is a kind of letdown.

71
00:04:06,260 --> 00:04:07,590
Time's up. I have to go.

72
00:04:07,590 --> 00:04:08,860
Second-tier schools are strict about discipline.

73
00:04:08,860 --> 00:04:11,070
Especially our school.

74
00:04:12,330 --> 00:04:15,480
Also, if you ever want to go somewhere, call me.

75
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:18,580
I'll take you. See you.

76
00:04:18,580 --> 00:04:20,080
Bye-bye.

77
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,690
   

78
00:04:31,350 --> 00:04:33,680
Gu Xuejiao, did you lie to me?

79
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,790
I've asked so many people at JUFE,

80
00:04:35,790 --> 00:04:38,650
but no one's seen Zhou Shiyun.

81
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:51,710
 Leave me alone! 

82
00:04:51,710 --> 00:04:53,200
 I said leave me alone! 

83
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:54,560
 But why? 

84
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:57,390
 How did things just fall apart like that? 

85
00:04:57,390 --> 00:05:00,510
 And in such an awkward way. 

86
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:02,760
 Do you want to hear the truth? 

87
00:05:10,220 --> 00:05:12,980
How is it that someone you used to see every day

88
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:16,000
just disappeared like that?

89
00:05:44,540 --> 00:05:46,340
Xuejiao, take a look.

90
00:05:46,340 --> 00:05:47,860
This...

91
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:49,460
Push a little harder.

92
00:05:49,460 --> 00:05:51,990
You're good!

93
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:57,170
Master, if Xiao Gao finds out we came to eat lunch together,

94
00:05:57,170 --> 00:05:59,200
will he be mad?

95
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:04,080
Didn't he insist on checking out the freshmen at the girls' dorm?

96
00:06:06,910 --> 00:06:08,900
- Looks good, huh? 
 - It actually does.

97
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:10,470
Isn't that Senior Brother Lin?

98
00:06:10,470 --> 00:06:11,790
Lin...

99
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:13,960
Is there a back door?

100
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:14,980
No.

101
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:17,500
We're a bit late.

102
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:22,740
Want to get some stir-fry?

103
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:26,390
How about some dessert?

104
00:06:26,390 --> 00:06:29,410
Master, since when do you eat dessert?

105
00:06:34,730 --> 00:06:37,110
Welcome.

106
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:47,980
You work here?

107
00:06:47,980 --> 00:06:52,563
I do. I'm a pastry apprentice now.

108
00:06:52,563 --> 00:06:55,230
Have you seen Gu Xuejiao today?

109
00:06:55,230 --> 00:06:57,260
Gu Xuejiao?

110
00:06:58,710 --> 00:07:00,370
No.

111
00:07:00,370 --> 00:07:03,900
It's just me and my mentor here today.

112
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:06,200
I didn't ask about that.

113
00:07:07,220 --> 00:07:10,590
I thought you were here to do a health inspection.

114
00:07:10,590 --> 00:07:13,450
Master, which one do you want to try?

115
00:07:15,063 --> 00:07:16,623
This one.

116
00:07:19,810 --> 00:07:21,270
¥20.

117
00:07:25,350 --> 00:07:26,790
Thanks, you two.

118
00:07:26,790 --> 00:07:28,030
The two of us?

119
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:30,120
Come again next time.

120
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:32,350
Grandmaster, do you want to try that one?

121
00:07:33,450 --> 00:07:35,080
How about that stir-fry?

122
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:41,100
Xuejiao, why didn't you say hi to Senior Brother Lin?

123
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:43,470
Grown-up stuff, stay out of it. Just make your desserts.

124
00:07:43,470 --> 00:07:45,880
Does he have dirt on you or something?

125
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:46,900
Come on, tell me.

126
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,120
What's wrong?

127
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:50,640
You... just do your work.

128
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:53,970
Why can't I know what's going on?

129
00:07:53,970 --> 00:07:55,520
You...

130
00:07:55,520 --> 00:08:00,320
You... if you don't tell me, I'm never making you those delicious little cakes again.

131
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:02,080
It's... It's nothing.

132
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:03,770
Really.

133
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:07,080
   

134
00:08:07,080 --> 00:08:08,221
Heavens. 
    

135
00:08:08,221 --> 00:08:09,680
School just started.

136
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,730
And you're so intense already?

137
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:11,860
After military training,

138
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:14,350
we have the entrance test coming up.

139
00:08:14,350 --> 00:08:15,930
Let's go out and look around a little.

140
00:08:15,930 --> 00:08:19,390
By junior year, I'll be in the school's Elite Program and study abroad.

141
00:08:19,390 --> 00:08:20,730
I have to start preparing now.

142
00:08:20,730 --> 00:08:22,810
Wh... What program?

143
00:08:22,810 --> 00:08:25,590
Here. I might as well show it to all of you.

144
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:30,220
These are the elite overseas universities partnered with our school.

145
00:08:30,220 --> 00:08:32,050
Limited spots.

146
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:34,300
I only recognize the first three. 
    

147
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:35,850
Those are world-famous top-tier schools.

148
00:08:35,850 --> 00:08:38,220
Who doesn't know about them?

149
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:42,610
Still, I'd suggest you get familiar with the ones lower on the list, too.

150
00:08:42,610 --> 00:08:44,010
Look at Zhao Feifei.

151
00:08:44,010 --> 00:08:45,750
She skipped a grade and took the big exam early.

152
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:47,100
And then there's Si Qi.

153
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:49,670
She was the top scorer in the whole province.

154
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:53,560
Feifei, do you want to study abroad, too?

155
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:56,630
Actually, I'm not really happy with my current major.

156
00:08:56,630 --> 00:09:00,370
I'm thinking of switching fields for grad school.

157
00:09:00,370 --> 00:09:02,340
Go into aerospace flight control.

158
00:09:02,340 --> 00:09:03,470
Build rockets someday.

159
00:09:03,470 --> 00:09:05,480
Maybe become an astronaut.

160
00:09:06,730 --> 00:09:08,280
Look at my build.

161
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:10,660
If I join the Space Station as a payload specialist,

162
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:13,740
wouldn't I be a lot lighter than everyone else?

163
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:16,130
Great idea.

164
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:18,300
No wonder you skipped a grade.

165
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:22,010
Si Qi.

166
00:09:22,010 --> 00:09:23,440
What textbook are you reading?

167
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,470
Let me in on it, too.

168
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:27,470
This is civil service exam prep.

169
00:09:27,470 --> 00:09:29,060
You're preparing for that this early?

170
00:09:29,060 --> 00:09:31,100
That's just how Si Qi studies.

171
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:33,370
Otherwise, how could she be the top scorer?

172
00:09:33,370 --> 00:09:35,220
That's called the Matthew Effect.

173
00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:37,820
The better you are, the better you get.

174
00:09:37,820 --> 00:09:41,010
The biggest highlight of your life is probably just getting into Jinghai University.

175
00:09:41,010 --> 00:09:44,700
You want to enter the real world with only that degree?

176
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:46,650
 Shu Lan is right. 

177
00:09:46,650 --> 00:09:49,650
 I barely scraped into Jinghai University. 

178
00:09:49,650 --> 00:09:52,650
 Everyone here has a clear goal. 

179
00:09:52,650 --> 00:09:54,100
 But me? 

180
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:59,780
 Was getting in here the endgame for me? 

181
00:09:59,780 --> 00:10:01,630
Let's stop studying for a little while.

182
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:04,050
Let's break the ice.

183
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:09,340
   
   

184
00:10:09,340 --> 00:10:11,235
    
 There's a bug in this code.

185
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:13,380
Double-check it.

186
00:10:20,340 --> 00:10:23,610
   
   

187
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:27,610
   

188
00:10:27,610 --> 00:10:29,650
Xuejiao's calling.

189
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,609
Hello?

190
00:10:38,609 --> 00:10:39,817
Hello?

191
00:10:39,817 --> 00:10:42,427
This is Gu Xuejiao.

192
00:10:43,220 --> 00:10:44,530
What's up?

193
00:10:44,530 --> 00:10:48,860
I just sent you a red packet.

194
00:10:49,980 --> 00:10:51,987
I received it.

195
00:10:51,987 --> 00:10:57,967
So, could you return it?

196
00:11:03,220 --> 00:11:04,890
Return it?

197
00:11:05,750 --> 00:11:08,720
Yes, it wasn't meant for you, actually.

198
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,340
 I'm sorry. 

199
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:11,590
Okay.

200
00:11:11,590 --> 00:11:13,200
I'll return it.

201
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,710
Thanks.

202
00:11:14,710 --> 00:11:16,600
Wait.

203
00:11:21,282 --> 00:11:24,850
You said it wasn't for me. So who was it supposed to go to?

204
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:26,620
I...

205
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:30,032
Hang up. Hang up.

206
00:11:30,032 --> 00:11:33,770
Right, how could I make that mistake?

207
00:11:33,770 --> 00:11:36,500
Gu Xuejiao, listen, once military training is over,

208
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:37,800
there's the placement test.

209
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:39,680
Quit messing around.

210
00:11:40,590 --> 00:11:43,640
I'm so sorry to bother you. Don't forget to return it.

211
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:46,250
Hey!

212
00:11:48,770 --> 00:11:50,410
It's not even a holiday.

213
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:53,090
Why did she send a red packet?

214
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,370
Hurry up.

215
00:12:04,370 --> 00:12:06,630
The clock is ticking.

216
00:12:08,350 --> 00:12:10,280
Xuejiao just started college, and here you are,

217
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:12,270
acting like a teacher with me.

218
00:12:13,756 --> 00:12:15,956
You haven't seen her either?

219
00:12:24,220 --> 00:12:25,590
 Why have you been avoiding me lately? 

220
00:12:25,590 --> 00:12:27,640
 I haven't. 

221
00:12:30,410 --> 00:12:31,680
 I really haven't. 

222
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:34,110
 I'm still adjusting to the new environment. 

223
00:12:34,110 --> 00:12:36,540
 I'll be fine in a little while. 

224
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:42,680
She just got here.

225
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:45,370
She's still adjusting.

226
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:54,040
 As long as you live long enough, the tables will turn. 

227
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:56,370
 I wish you a long life. 

228
00:12:59,060 --> 00:12:59,969
   

229
00:12:59,969 --> 00:13:01,040
 Mr. Lin, 

230
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:04,830
 I know a lot of top firms have made you offers. 

231
00:13:04,830 --> 00:13:09,510
 But we're coming to you with 110% passion and sincerity. 

232
00:13:09,510 --> 00:13:13,590
 So, we really hope you'll give this some serious thought. 

233
00:13:18,568 --> 00:13:20,128
 Babe. 

234
00:13:22,110 --> 00:13:23,502
 You came to pick me up? 

235
00:13:23,502 --> 00:13:26,560
 After all, you're more important than work. 

236
00:13:26,560 --> 00:13:30,460
 Great. Listen, let me take you to that amazing place tonight. 

237
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:34,510
We've been staying up for days.

238
00:13:34,510 --> 00:13:39,530
Bro, look. We haven't taken a single day off since then.

239
00:13:40,230 --> 00:13:41,800
- If we keep this up... 
  - I even gave up an offer 

240
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:44,140
 to become a full-time employee in my original position. 

241
00:13:44,140 --> 00:13:47,440
 Director Lin, I truly value this opportunity. 
   

242
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,200
 Today is 5 September. 

243
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:52,510
   

244
00:13:52,510 --> 00:13:53,800
Nice one, you guys.

245
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:55,870
Two rounds of the same insane task?

246
00:13:55,870 --> 00:13:58,400
It's not our fault you picked it twice in a row.

247
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,800
How's that, Si Qi?

248
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:01,530
Thrilling, huh?

249
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,680
Won't he get the wrong idea?

250
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:10,040
Something's going on between you...

251
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:11,470
Stop.

252
00:14:11,470 --> 00:14:13,350
I'm just worried he'll figure out this is a prank.

253
00:14:13,350 --> 00:14:15,830
Next time I see him, it will be so awkward.

254
00:14:15,830 --> 00:14:17,160
Tell us the truth.

255
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:19,690
Who's this Mr. "Life Is Precious"?

256
00:14:21,590 --> 00:14:22,710
Don't try to trick me.

257
00:14:22,710 --> 00:14:25,560
We're playing "Dare," not "Truth".

258
00:14:25,560 --> 00:14:27,256
I'm not playing.

259
00:14:27,256 --> 00:14:30,080
Hey, Xuejiao, you were the one who suggested an icebreaker.

260
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,440
Right.

261
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,710
Can't handle the heat now?

262
00:14:32,710 --> 00:14:34,480
That's right, I can't.

263
00:14:37,560 --> 00:14:42,200
What are we going to do, Si Qi?

264
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,750
- Tell us! 
 - Okay.

265
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:45,280
I would have told you if I knew!

266
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:46,400
Speak up!

267
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:51,080
- Tell us... 
 - No!

268
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:56,470
At least, he was right about one thing.

269
00:14:56,470 --> 00:14:58,910
