551
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:21,920
Starting tomorrow. Next.

552
00:33:24,890 --> 00:33:27,310
Lin Jiadong really said that?

553
00:33:27,310 --> 00:33:29,320
Word for word. Really.

554
00:33:29,320 --> 00:33:33,730
That chief of staff of yours is so sarcastic, like some mean old witch.

555
00:33:33,730 --> 00:33:37,540
He's got the tiniest little mind, like a pea.

556
00:33:39,840 --> 00:33:41,791
That's kind of true.

557
00:33:41,791 --> 00:33:43,930
But you barely even know him.

558
00:33:43,930 --> 00:33:45,560
Don't jump to conclusions.

559
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:46,730
Give it some time.

560
00:33:46,730 --> 00:33:48,560
 I didn't jump to conclusions at all. 

561
00:33:48,560 --> 00:33:49,890
 I know him way too well. 

562
00:33:49,890 --> 00:33:52,120
I am just stating facts here.

563
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:54,790
Besides, if this is how your lab recruits,

564
00:33:54,790 --> 00:33:59,070
you'll be missing out on a lot of talents like me.

565
00:34:06,490 --> 00:34:09,200
Just a few days ago, you were avoiding me.

566
00:34:09,200 --> 00:34:12,750
Why do you want to get into our lab now?

567
00:34:13,410 --> 00:34:18,090
